Data processing
In the following, we inform you about the collection of personal data when using our website, services and contact form. The service provider in accordance with § 13 of the German Telemedia Act and the responsible body in accordance with Art. 4 No. 7 DSGVO is Headup GmbH see I.
Personal data is all data that can be related to you personally, for example name, address, email addresses, user behaviour. For the rest, we refer to Art. 4 No. 1 DSGVO, the legal definition.
In the case of mere information use of the website, i.e. if you do not log in to use the website, register or otherwise send us information, we do not collect any personal data with the exception of the data that your browser transmits to enable you to visit the website and this contact form.
These are:
IP address
Date and time of the request, time zone difference to GMT
Content of the request (specific page)
access status
Amount of data transferred in each case
Website from which the request came
browser
Operating systems and their interface
Language and version of the browser software
If you use our contact form, additional:
Name
Email address
Our website uses so-called cookies. These are small text files that are stored on your end device with the help of the browser. They do not cause any damage. We use cookies to make our website user-friendly. Some cookies remain stored on your end device until you delete them. They enable us to recognise your browser on your next visit. If you do not wish this, you can set your browser so that it informs you about the setting of cookies and you only allow this in individual cases.
We only use technically necessary cookies and no cookies from thirdparty providers.
