Disclosure of data
Your personal data will not be transferred to third parties for purposes other than those listed below.
We will only share your personal information with third parties if:
you have given your express consent in accordance with Art. 6 para. 1 sentence 1 lit. a DSGVO;
the disclosure is necessary for the assertion, exercise or defence of legal claims pursuant to Art. 6 (1) sentence 1 lit. f DSGVO and there is no reason to assume that you have a predominantly legitimate interest in the non-disclosure of your data;
there is a legal obligation for the disclosure in accordance with Art. 6 para. 1 sentence 1 lit. c DSGVO as well as;
this is legally permissible and necessary for the processing of contractual relationships with you according to Art. 6 para. 1 p. 1 lit. b DSGVO.
Data processing in our games
In our games, we can track and analyse various actions at the player level to improve the game experience and the stability of the application. For example, the data collected allows us to check whether the application is working properly around the world. The data is also used to identify and fix software bugs when they occur. No data such as images, documents or other personal data unrelated to the application is accessed or collected by the application. Our collection and use of data helps to ensure that you can access your games as easily as possible and get the best service and gaming experience we have to offer.
This includes, in particular, contact data provided during registration and your actions in the game. In addition, we collect your connection data, such as the IP address. The processing of this information is necessary for the implementation of the game operation and is therefore carried out on the legal basis of Art. 6 Para. 1 Sentence. 1 Letter b DSGVO.
The personal data collected, used and processed is stored on our servers and on the servers of the following service providers cooperating with us.
